  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x201C;Provision of health care and medical services for the vulnerable groups of IDPs and hosting community residing in Al-Raml Al-Janoubi ,the city, and the north rural of Lattakia governorate.&#x201C;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Child Care Association is a Non-profit association  which care for the families and their children since their first year of birth. And it takes care of widows, the elderly and the women headed households. CCA also provide them with  medical and social care.
Since the NGO has a medical center and  deals with health sector for long time (over 40 years) and during the crisis in Syria the medical center continued its work helping people in need especially the residents in Alramel Aljanoubi neighborhoods-which is near- where many IDPs rented or stayed, as well as the displaced people living in the north rural of Lattakia and the plan to reach them in this project will be by linking with some of the NGOs in that area, as well as doing focus groups in that area to announce our work.
These two targeted areas are inhabited by the poorest population in the city and during this crisis it has become overcrowded by the internally displaced arrivals from other governorates.  The latest estimation of the displaced people in Lattakia are about 449000 persons , this is the number of the IDPs according to OCHA records and the number is increasing more by the time of speaking  . Therefore, the medical and non-medical services no longer meet the increasing needs.

Based on the need assessment conducted by CCA, the proposed project will focus on the following activities: 

-Provision of life-sustaining health services by covering the costs of 400 surgical operations to most vulnerable groups who cannot afford (IDPs and host community) 70% of beneficiaries are women and children. The priorities are caesarean / normal deliveries and orthopedic operations and cancer chemical doses for children.) 

- Providing financial support to referral cases and prescriptions (for unavailable medicines in the health center) for 2600 patients
The association health center can receive patients from Alramel Aljanoubi and the near bye rural and  provide its services for them for free.</narrative>
  </description>
